messages.message: just wanted to follow up on this, i might have missed if there was a resolution put into place.

models trained on older versions will work on newer versions. models trained on new versions won’t work on old versions

it’s like how an app made for iOS 14 will work on iOS 15, but it won’t work the other way around.

how many clients have this issue? i know upgrading takes time, but them upgrading to 22.01 will be quicker/more reliable than us trying to make+test a patch for 21.10
@alagar is this tracker (https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1RJZvutRiwdM7FBT8lfJqJxmULfbjNv-0yMSD8-zVIEM/edit#gid=0) up to date? looks like GS, SC, natwest, and BofA @peter
that’s the old release - we’re using this one now https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1H2DMx8zyLwLV072rblsh8wjeAVMDtpsm33hcoUmmfwA/edit?pli=1#gid=0 (i think alagar has been updating this too)
